| Traditional NLP + ML                                  | NLP + Deep Learning                                                           |
| ----------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Manual feature extraction (Bag of Words, TF-IDF)      | Learns features automatically from data                                       |
| Algorithms like Naive Bayes, SVM, Logistic Regression | Neural networks like LSTM, GRU, Transformer                                   |
| Works well on smaller datasets                        | Excels with large datasets                                                    |
| Limited understanding of context                      | Strong understanding of context and semantics                                 |
| Faster to train                                       | Typically requires more computation                                           |
| Good for simpler classification tasks                 | Best for complex tasks like translation, summarization, and conversational AI |


=====================


NLP teaches a computer to work with human language,

while Deep Learning gives it the ability to learn language patterns, context, and meaning automatically, 
enabling powerful applications such as chatbots, translation systems, sentiment analysis, and text generation.

